column5: Good Gawd....That was nasty.. I cant think for even a second that that kid survived that one...
A little faster and he might have cleared the bridge.
Ya, I saw that on a TV show.  Absolutely crazy. The car broke apart around him, and he kept going.
the reference to micheal knight is classic.

Speed kills folks....just watch this crash test to see for yourself..Note thou this is very graphic no humans get hurt..It is a must see for anyone with a lead foot    <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/l4PjSVOnrVg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
WOW, brutal.  That's sure something to think about!!!!
they should show this over and over and over and over, to some of the total ijuts i see on the road every single day i drive. Problem is, some of them would think that this vid is COOL

COOOL !!  Oh.. and remember, if you are gonna head on someone be sure to accelerate so you become the cement wall !  ...and the error in the video. That is not the same as two vehicles doing 120mph hitting head on.. that simulates two vehicles doing 60 mph hitting head on.
Take wreckages like that and put them on a pedestal at every on-ramp onto the 401.  Safer driving ensues.
like Irishfield said 60 mph head on crash
Though it does simulate pretty well one of my old teenhood friends hitting a bridge abutment @ somewhere beyond 150 MPH in his 'Cuda though.
I shoulda known
Not quite guys, second car's (in a head on 60mph x2 crash) "crumble" zone would negate some of the impact where as the wall had very little, if any.

Oh definitely Rob... just pointing out a narrative mistake in the video. Two vehicles at 120mph would make more mess !  My old (dead) buddy didn't move the bridge abutment either... but we did get to salvage his Dana 60 locker rear differential.
not if the second vehicle was a mack truck and a full load of cement
Still "better" then the wall. Didn't the mythbusters do something like this?

PFF.. myth busters. They also claimed that you can't chain a police car to a light standard and pull it's rear axle out from under it. I personally know that one is obtainable when you pick on an LTD...
Ah, we own a Focus,that didnt help.But then again,it,s her car,so I drive it slower then my truck  .  Must remember not to show this to the mrs,s

lol
